You are given the JSON data for one pull request from a codebase's evolution timeline. Visually describe a wide establishing view of this PR's place in the codebase's evolution — its scale, which parts of the codebase (districts) it touched, and its one-line hook. This is the first, broadest look at the PR.

PR data (level: PR Landscape):
{
  "pr": 2,
  "date": "2026-07-22",
  "title": "docs: add CLAUDE.md with codebase orientation + artifact feasibility findings",
  "tagline": "This PR proposes a single orientation doc so future sessions stop re-deriving the same layout and feasibility findings from scratch.",
  "depth": "detailed",
  "size": {
    "files": 1,
    "adds": 141,
    "dels": 0
  },
  "touched": {
    "(root)": 1
  },
  "adrs": [],
  "levels": {
    "landscape": {
      "narration": "This PR adds one new file, CLAUDE.md, 141 lines, at the repo root — no code changes.",
      "voice": "This PR is a documentation-only change. It adds one new file, CLAUDE dot M D, at the root of the repo — one hundred forty-one lines, no code touched."
    },
    "problem_solution": {
      "problem": "prodyssey has no in-repo orientation document. A session starting cold has to reconstruct the bundle output shape, the `<target>/.odyssey/` write boundary, and the viewer's sibling-file/relative-path dependencies by reading `SKILL.md`, the scripts, and `viewer/index.html` directly every time — including re-deriving conclusions the project has already reached once, like whether `viewer/index.html` can ship as a Claude Artifact.",
      "solution": "This PR proposes `CLAUDE.md`: an orientation doc covering layout, the generation flow (prereq gate → baseline → per-PR sweep → verify), the bundle output shape, and — grounded in an actual throwaway export built and published this session — the finding that the viewer is not artifact-safe as-is (sibling `<script src>` data loading, relative asset/audio paths, two external CDN calls) but renders correctly once flattened, with the 16 MiB cap and audio's ~33% base64 inflation named as the real constraint on a future export mode.",
      "narration": "Right now, understanding how this plugin's pieces fit together means reading the skill file and every script from scratch. This PR proposes writing that understanding down once — including a real experiment that already answered whether the bundle viewer could be published directly as a Claude Artifact.",
      "beats": [
        {
          "kind": "background",
          "text": "prodyssey's only structure-documenting file is `skills/odyssey/SKILL.md`, which describes orchestration procedure, not repo layout or bundle-shape conventions a session needs before touching code."
        },
        {
          "kind": "background",
          "text": "The viewer (`viewer/index.html`) depends on three things not visible from reading it alone: sibling `<script src=\"../data/*.js\">` tags populating `window.STORY`/`ODYSSEY`/`DIFFS`/`ADRS`, relative asset/audio paths, and two external CDN requests (Google Fonts, jsdelivr Motion) — none of which are obvious without having built and served a real bundle."
        },
        {
          "kind": "intuition",
          "text": "Concretely: this session built a throwaway artifact-safe export earlier — literal JSON inlined for `window.STORY`/`ODYSSEY`/`DIFFS`/`ADRS`, asset paths rewritten to a `window.ODYSSEY_ASSETS` data-URI map, both CDN tags dropped — and it rendered correctly, PR nav/levels/hero image/audio dialog all worked. Without `CLAUDE.md`, the next session asking the same artifact-feasibility question would rebuild that same experiment instead of reading one paragraph."
        }
      ],
      "voice": "Before this PR, understanding how prodyssey's pieces fit together meant reading the orchestration skill and every script from scratch each time. This proposes writing that down once — including a real experiment, already run this session, that answered whether the bundle viewer could be published directly as a Claude Artifact."
    },
    "architecture": {
      "narration": "This PR touches no module boundary, dependency direction, or public interface — it is a documentation-only change with zero architecture decisions to record.",
      "voice": "This is a documentation-only change. It doesn't move a module boundary or a public interface, so there's no architecture decision to record here.",
      "beats": [
        {
          "kind": "boundary",
          "text": "Null decision: `CLAUDE.md` is prose only, added at the repo root. It doesn't move code between districts, add a dependency, or change any script's or the viewer's behavior — it only documents behavior and constraints (the artifact-feasibility finding, the bundle output shape) that already existed before this PR."
        }
      ]
    },
    "file_changes": {
      "narration": "One file added: CLAUDE.md, at the repo root.",
      "groups": [
        {
          "title": "Orientation doc",
          "note": "New file, no existing file touched — codebase layout, generation flow, bundle output shape, and the artifact-feasibility experiment writeup, so a future session doesn't reconstruct any of it from scratch.",
          "files": [
            "CLAUDE.md"
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  "status": "open"
}

